article.headline: Lehigh 64, Stony Brook 49
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Austen Rowland scored 19 points and Lehigh's aggressive defense forced 20 turnovers in a 64-49 victory over Stony Brook on Tuesday night. Earl Nurse, the only other Mountain Hawk in double digits, finished with 10 points and 7 rebounds. Lehigh trailed for most of the first half, shooting only 36.7 percent, and Stony Brook took a 26-25 lead into halftime on the strength of 5-of-10 3-point shooting. The Mountain Hawks started the second half on an 8-1 run to take a 34-27 lead. Stony Brook closed within 34-31, but another 11-3 run by Lehigh put the game out of reach. The Seawolves never got closer than six points the rest of the game. For Stony Brook, Mitchell Beauford had 13 points and Mike Popoko had 12. Stony Brook shot just 34 percent for the game and made only 7 of 14 free throws. Lehigh, which came up with 12 steals, scored 21 points off turnovers to Stony Brook's 4.
